public final class nanoproc
{
	public nanoproc()
	{
		optx = 1;
		optimes = new long[10];
		lastcurh = System.nanoTime();
		curhead = System.nanoTime();
	}

	public int proc(int n)
	{
		long l = 1000000L * (long) n;
		curhead += calcf();
		if (lastcurh > curhead)
		{
			misc.sleep((lastcurh - curhead) / 1000000L);
			last += lastcurh - curhead;
			curhead += lastcurh - curhead;
			lastcurh += l;
			return 1;
		}
		n = 0;
		do
		{
			lastcurh += l;
			n++;
		}
		while (n != 10 && curhead > lastcurh);
		if (curhead > lastcurh)
			lastcurh = curhead;

		return n;
	}

	public void push()
	{
		last = 0L;
		if (lastcurh > curhead)
			curhead += lastcurh - curhead;

	}

	public long cur()
	{
		return curhead;
	}

	private long calcf()
	{
		long l = System.nanoTime();
		long l1 = l - last;
		last = l;
		if (l1 > -5000000000L && l1 < 5000000000L)
		{
			optimes[optpos] = l1;
			if (optx < 1)
				optx++;

			optpos = (optpos + 1) % 10;
		}
		l1 = 0L;
		for (int n = 1; optx >= n; n++)
			l1 += optimes[(optpos + 10 - n) % 10];

		return l1 / (long) optx;
	}

	private int optx;
	private int optpos;
	private long lastcurh;
	private long curhead;
	private long last;
	private long[] optimes;
}
